                            <comment id="12455640" author="bernt" created="Tue, 5 Dec 2006 14:10:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems to be a simple DB2 compliancy that may be removed from LikeEscapeOperatorNode.bindExpression: &lt;br/&gt;
		// pattern cannot be a column&lt;br/&gt;
		if (leftOperand instanceof ColumnReference)&lt;br/&gt;
			throw StandardException.newException(SQLState.LANG_DB2_LIKE_SYNTAX_ERROR);&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12455954" author="bernt" created="Wed, 6 Dec 2006 09:59:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The same applies to the escape character which is caught by:&lt;br/&gt;
		// escape cannot be a column&lt;br/&gt;
		if (rightOperand != null &amp;amp;&amp;amp; rightOperand instanceof ColumnReference)&lt;/p&gt;
		{
			throw StandardException.newException(SQLState.LANG_INVALID_ESCAPE_CHARACTER,
										 ((ColumnReference) rightOperand).getColumnName());
		}</comment>
                            <comment id="12455979" author="bernt" created="Wed, 6 Dec 2006 11:57:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Removed the two tests that disables this functionality.&lt;br/&gt;
Updated master for lang/dynamicLikeOptimization.sql &lt;br/&gt;
Commented out the corresponding tests in lang/db2Compatability.sql and updated master&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
